<L>__{exterior a cigar store day}
<A>__{doyle already beginning to feel the cold, rubbing his hands together, at the front of the place charnier and nicoli have entered, trying to figure it out as charnier and nicoli emerge, charnier ripping the cellophane off a pack of cigarettes, and they turn back in doyle's direction. doyle, face to face with charnier and nicoli. straining to hear, he picks up a few words of french. without losing stride he steps off the curb and cuts across the street, moving south, away from them, as they come north. but halfway across the street, we pick up russo coming in his direction, sharp enough to pick up the tail where doyle had to drop it.}
